content.description:
Yabo cave heads out of a cave downgradient to the left about 15 feet from the highest point on the rock. The route heads out of the deep (approx. 6 feet) cave and up the huecos to a committing mantle finish.

Pads are good for both the tree and for the ensuing fall from the mantle or the slap into the final hueco.
content.protection: At least 1 pad, and probably 2-3. If you've got extra, wrap one around the tree to the left of the problem.

content.description: Sit start and slap up to a good crimp and do a couple more moves to top out. Fun slopers to rare positive hold top out.
Crux is with right hand on highest crimp and left hand on start hold, moving left hand up to tiny flake with thumbcatch and crappy heelhook. the movement isnt hard at all, the crimps are just so bad.
content.protection: One bouldering pad will do, make sure you cover all the rocks.
content.location: To the left of yabo roof, just outside of the cave. Its to the left of the tree next to yabo roof and it starts left hand on a crimp rail and right hand on a crimp.

content.description: Start on a slopey undercling with good feet. Then make some big slappy moves up to better holds. Top out. The first move is the crux. While is it mossy, and not a great boulder, the sculpted slopey features are pretty cool.
content.location: On the back side of the boulder, if you are coming around the right side past Pockets and the tree.

content.description:
The Tree Problem sits on the uphill side of The Parking Lot Boulder, strangely enough no where near a tree.  Climbing is sustained, and many approaches can get you through the problem depending on your height and finger size.

Top out over the top after 8 or so hard moves and a good rest in the middle.
Sit start on the the huge jug and climb straight up and slightly right to a mega sloper topout without moving left to a better hold used for flakes I beleive.
content.location: Left of pockets, right of flakes.

content.description: Start with undercling on a prow, then go straight up

Sit start then make way up the bulging, leaning Arete using the big hole, a couple small crimps, and the giant sloper. Committing top. Finish just right of the tree.

Left edge of the Arete and giant hueco stuff to the left of it are off, except to start. Tree off.

A couple clips of Sharma doing this route in the movie, Rampage. So… Rampage Arete. If there’s an older name and FA please edit. Also guessing on grade - didn’t find any info.
content.location: Lower Arete on the side of Parking Lot Rock facing the trail as you walk to it from the parking lot.

content.description: Sit start as for the Tree Problem and finish on Deforestation. Much better than The original Tree Problem imo.

Climb the pocketed face. Finish left of the tree.

A little unnerving with the tree right there.
content.protection: Not much will help you avoid the tree. I guess pads and spotters.
content.location: Downhill side of Parking Lot Rock

content.description: Start low and climb the offwidth without using the big jug on the V0. Technical
content.location: In between the tree route and the V0 warm-up

content.description: Kind of a one move wonder. Stand start on the good hold and lie back up.
content.protection: Pad would be nice but not needed.
content.location: On the left side of the uphill face of parking lot rock. Right of Coz Mama. Left of Deforestation.

content.description: Starting on a decent right sidepull and a decent left sloper, move up to a huge Hueco and jug sidepull.  Delicately move up to a small left crimp on top, and a micro crimp edge on the right.  Finally,  finish on the blunt right arete and top out.  Crux is moving off the small crimps and topping out.  ***The landing area has a multiple tree roots and small boulders on a downhill slope.  Take care in spotting and padding the landing as this is a highball problem.***
lieback the right facing flakes straight up
content.location: Around the corner from tree route (oposite side of Yabo roof)

content.description:
Begin the sit start under Deforestation with an obvious right sidepull and left edge, go up through a left shouldery move and straight to Deforestation.

https://youtu.be/wDAFPL9Kf1o

climbs.name: Deforestation
climbs.fa: Mike A, Kent S, and Rouke B

content.description:
Ascend small crimps on the steep wall to the left of the Tree Problem. The crux is a hard throw off painful crimps which keep breaking due to people climbing too soon after rainstorms. As a result the move keeps getting longer and harder. Remember to wait at least 48 hours after storms before climbing this problem.

A sit start to this problem exists which has a suggested grade of V12. Begin the sit start under Deforestation with a obviously right sidepull and left edge, go up through a left shouldery move and straight to Deforestation. First documented ascent; Francesco Spadea 2020.
content.location: Located just left of the Tree Problem. This problem is where "the tree" used to be.

content.description: Start on the holds for Deforestation and go big moves right and up to top out the Tree Problem.
content.location: Parking lot rock - Deforestation stand start (both hands close together on side pulls - left in a small flare crack and right on a crimp).

content.description:
Sit Start to Coz Mama. There are a couple variations, but the crux is starting low with arms spread, and getting matched on the Coz Mama start hold (large, rounded crimp right at the lip) without dabbing on the rock or pads below, and then topping out. Consensus from 10+ ticks were all 7b or 7b+ (V8/-) on 8anu at time of this Entry. FA suggested 7b+ there too.

Adding a long move straight out to the side jug after the coz mama start is also fun (instead of using a left hand sloper first). Then you can also go further out right from there and finish up the Lieback V1 for an extra move or two - which people are calling Power Traverse.
content.protection: Thin pad or two is useful
content.location: Parking lot rock between Coz Daddy and The Lieback.

content.description: To the right of Yabo roof is another little roof problem.  Start, sitting on the large ledge and  pull up to the right through some slopers.
Start matched on lower rail or down deeper in the cave (won't effect the grade) climb right under bulge.  Do some weird moves to catch a  two or three finger pocket and hump the rock as you top out.
content.location: backside of parking lot boulder. just right of Yabo Roof

content.description:
to the left of deforestation. high start on two crimps and go straight up.

Several variations exist which can make this route slightly easier or harder. You choose.
